title: Il buono, il brutto, il cattivo
overview: A bounty hunting scam joins two men in an uneasy alliance against a third in a race to find a fortune in gold buried in a remote cemetery.

title: Once Upon a Time in the West
overview: A mysterious stranger with a harmonica joins forces with a notorious desperado to protect a beautiful widow from a ruthless assassin working for the railroad.

title: The Magdalene Sisters
overview: Three young Irish women struggle to maintain their spirits while they endure dehumanizing abuse as inmates of a Magdalene Sisters Asylum.

title: The Color Purple
overview: A black Southern woman struggles to find her identity after suffering abuse from her father and others over four decades.

title: Midnight Cowboy
overview: A naive hustler travels from Texas to New York City to seek personal fortune, finding a new friend in the process.

title: The Deer Hunter
overview: An in-depth examination of the ways in which the U.S. Vietnam War impacts and disrupts the lives of people in a small industrial town in Pennsylvania.

title: Gran Torino
overview: Disgruntled Korean War veteran Walt Kowalski sets out to reform his neighbor, Thao Lor, a Hmong teenager who tried to steal Kowalski's prized possession: a 1972 Gran Torino.

title: Kis Uykusu
overview: A hotel owner and landlord in a remote Turkish village deals with conflicts within his family and a tenant behind on his rent.

title: A Christmas Story
overview: In the 1940s, a young boy named Ralphie attempts to convince his parents, his teacher and Santa that a Red Ryder BB gun really is the perfect Christmas gift.

title: The Florida Project
overview: Set over one summer, the film follows precocious six-year-old Moonee as she courts mischief and adventure with her ragtag playmates and bonds with her rebellious but caring mother, all while living in the shadows of Walt Disney World.

title: The Visitor
overview: A college professor travels to New York City to attend a conference and finds a young couple living in his apartment.

title: Dead Poets Society
overview: Maverick teacher John Keating uses poetry to embolden his boarding school students to new heights of self-expression.

title: The Social Network
overview: As Harvard student Mark Zuckerberg creates the social networking site that would become known as Facebook, he is sued by the twins who claimed he stole their idea, and by the co-founder who was later squeezed out of the business.

title: The Bourne Ultimatum
overview: Jason Bourne dodges a ruthless C.I.A. official and his Agents from a new assassination program while searching for the origins of his life as a trained killer.

title: Soorarai Pottru
overview: Nedumaaran Rajangam "Maara" sets out to make the common man fly and in the process takes on the world's most capital intensive industry and several enemies who stand in his way.

title: Per qualche dollaro in più
overview: Two bounty hunters with the same intentions team up to track down a Western outlaw.
stars: ['Clint Eastwood', 'Lee Van Cleef', 'Gian Maria Volontè', 'Mara Krupp']

title: The Muppet Christmas Carol
overview: The Muppet characters tell their version of the classic tale of an old and bitter miser's redemption on Christmas Eve.

title: Annie Hall
overview: Neurotic New York comedian Alvy Singer falls in love with the ditzy Annie Hall.

title: Rain Man
overview: Selfish yuppie Charlie Babbitt's father left a fortune to his savant brother Raymond and a pittance to Charlie; they travel cross-country.

title: The Dark Knight Rises
overview: Eight years after the Joker's reign of anarchy, Batman, with the help of the enigmatic Catwoman, is forced from his exile to save Gotham City from the brutal guerrilla terrorist Bane.
